parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as it compromises the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbag light is on
airbag does not deploy during an accident
chemical burns from airbag deployment
injuries or fatalities due to lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of the airbag without a crash can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents, as well as unnecessary repair costs.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without an accident
injuries or damage from airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which may lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is on
inability to reset the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt latch can compromise the safety of the driver and passengers, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt latch does not securely fasten
the latch return spring breaks
the seat belt buckle does not latch securely
the seat belt hangs loose and does not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seat belt may not fit comfortably or securely, potentially causing discomfort, distraction, or even injury to the driver or passengers.
symptoms: The seat belt comes across the neck or body at an uncomfortable angle
the seat belt does not fit securely
the driver or passenger feels unsafe or uncomfortable wearing the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause unpredictable and intermittent failures of various vehicle systems, leading to a loss of critical functions, increased risk of accidents, and potentially even fires.
symptoms: The parking brake warning light comes on when the brake is off
dashboard lights
including speedometer
radio
and heat/air
go out without warning
interior passenger compartment lights fail to operate
electrical shorts
and fires in the engine compartment.
